{
  "texts": [
    "Unlike existing tool usage benchmarks, Tool-RoCo first conceptualizes agents as tools and agent uses other agents as tools to measure how LLM agents autonomously cooperate with other agents.",
    "• Tool-RoCo proposes two novel metrics: selforganization (SO) and cooperation-tool ratio(CT).",
    "Self-organization quantifies the degree to which an agent autonomously seeks assistance from other agents, and the cooperation-tool ratio is the proportion of cooperative tool usage.",
    "These two metrics provide a novel evaluation of the autonomy and cooperative capacities of LLM-based agents.",
    "• Four LLMs are used to test and verify three multi-robot cooperation tasks: CABINET, PACK, and SORT in Tool-RoCo."
  ]
}